<item>
            <title>[HTTPCORE-581] Wrong deadline calculation for non-blocking read operations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCORE-581</link>
                <project id="12310340" key="HTTPCORE">HttpComponents HttpCore</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Presently the internal data channel calculates the deadline of read operation based on the last read access. Naturally the last read operation timestamp on a persistent (kept-alive) HTTP connection usually points back at the previous message exchange&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/httpcomponents-core/blob/master/httpcore5/src/main/java/org/apache/hc/core5/reactor/InternalChannel.java#L64&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/httpcomponents-core/blob/master/httpcore5/src/main/java/org/apache/hc/core5/reactor/InternalChannel.java#L64&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
